title: Handmade Wooden Painted Dhangro (Nga Drum) with Foldable Handles & Sung Inside
description:
This type of drum is a little bigger and a rounded version of the Damaru. It comes with a holder
hence it a little comfortable to hold comparatively. Nga (རྔ་) or drums are used widely in Bhutan as
musical instruments for religious rituals or for folk music and performances. Made with Sisam wood
Size chart (Diameter, Height) Small 16" 5.5" Large 20" 7" *approximately For custom sizes, please
reach us at our Customer Service. https://folkbazar.com/pages/contact-us
